<P><STRONG>November</STRONG></P>
<P>The holidays will be here before we know it, and planning for the 2012 International CES® is officially in high gear! To ensure you're getting the most out of your CES experience, check out our upcoming CES events and deadlines:</P>
<P>The 2012 Exhibitor PR Newsletter is distributed on the first Thursday of every month to all CES Exhibitor PR Contacts. We also host our past editions online.</P>
<P>This month's highlighted <STRONG>PR Opportunities</STRONG> include:</P>
<P>• Last Chance for CES Unveiled@London<BR>• Regional Media Outreach<BR>• Scheduling Exhibitor Press Conferences<BR>• Pre-Registered Media List<BR>• Press Kit preparation<BR>• Online Press Center<BR>• Hot Product Submissions CEA's Digital Answer Man and Press Pitch<BR>• CES Preview Involvement<BR>• CESTV<BR>• CNET Best of CES <BR>• The Official International CES Daily, produced by TWICE<BR>• Entertainment Matters Daily, produced by Variety<BR>• Upcoming Deadlines</P>
<P><STRONG>Last Chance for CES Unveiled@London<BR></STRONG>CES Unveiled@London<BR>November 17, 2011<BR>Inmarsat Conference Center, London, United Kingdom </P>
<P>The Consumer Electronics Association is taking CES Unveiled international with the new CES Unveiled @ London. Don't miss this opportunity to get your product in front of key UK media and analysts, just in time to make headlines before the holiday selling season. The Western European CE market is expected to exceed $221 billion in 2011. Sign up today to jumpstart your CES success and promote your services and products to the UK and European marketplace. Download the CES Unveiled @ London event brochure for more information.&nbsp; </P>
<P><STRONG>Regional Media Outreach</STRONG></P>
<P>CES publicizes its exhibitors and their products and technologies to the media in their respective geographic regions. The regional releases are a great (and free) way to get your company's show news publicized in your region's top outlets in the weeks leading up to CES. <BR>Submit a short quote (75 words or less) about your company's participation at CES to PRContacts@CE.org. Each release will contain approximately four quotes and inclusion is first-come, first-serve. The deadline for inclusion is November 21, 2011. <BR>The quote must be from a high-level executive and highlight anything new and exciting your company plans to showcase, and why you think CES is important to your company's success. When submitting a quote, make sure to include company name and headquarter location.</P>
<P><STRONG>Sample Quote<BR></STRONG>"We look forward to participating in the 2012 International CES because it offers unparalleled business opportunities and is the very best venue to launch our new products," said John Doe, president and CEO of Exhibitor X, based in location Y. "This year we are showcasing [your product or service name], our latest consumer technology product and announcing several key partnerships." </P>
<P>The releases will be distributed to the following regions in mid-December: <BR><BR>--- Northeast --- <BR>• Connecticut <BR>• New Hampshire <BR>• New Jersey<BR>• Maine&nbsp; <BR>• Rhode Island <BR>• New York<BR>• Massachusetts <BR>• Vermont <BR>• Pennsylvania<BR>&nbsp;<BR>--- Midwest --- <BR>• Indiana <BR>• Ohio <BR>• Iowa&nbsp; <BR>• Nebraska<BR>• Illinois&nbsp; <BR>• Wisconsin <BR>• Kansas <BR>• N. Dakota<BR>• Michigan <BR>• Minnesota<BR>• S. Dakota<BR>• Missouri<BR>&nbsp;<BR>--- South --- <BR>• Delaware <BR>• N. Carolina <BR>• Alabama <BR>• Arkansas<BR>• D.C.&nbsp; <BR>• S. Carolina<BR>• Kentucky <BR>• Louisiana<BR>• Florida&nbsp; <BR>• Virginia <BR>• Mississippi<BR>• Oklahoma<BR>• Georgia <BR>• West Virginia&nbsp;&nbsp; <BR>• Tennessee <BR>• Texas&nbsp; <BR>• Maryland <BR>--- West ---<BR>&nbsp;<BR>• Arizona <BR>• Montana <BR>• Alaska&nbsp; <BR>• Washington <BR>• Colorado <BR>• Utah&nbsp; <BR>• California <BR>• Idaho&nbsp; <BR>• Nevada <BR>• Hawaii<BR>• New Mexico <BR>• Wyoming <BR>• Oregon<BR>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <BR>--- International ---<BR>• Outside of the United States</P>
<P><STRONG>Scheduling Exhibitor Press Conferences<BR></STRONG>Exhibitor press conference scheduling for the 2012 International CES is quickly filling up, and a complete Exhibitor Press Event Schedule is now available. A press conference at CES is an excellent way to debut new products and make major company announcements. All CES exhibitors are eligible to hold a newsworthy press conference and have their event included on the official CES press event list. Full details are in the press conferences section of the 2012 Exhibitor PR Kit. We currently have the following press conference times available:</P>
<P>Monday, January 9, 2012<BR>Press Day, CLOSED. We are no longer accepting any press conference requests for Press Day.</P>
<P>Tuesday, January 10, 2012<BR>LVCC: 7:30-8:30 a.m. <BR>Venetian: 12:30-1:30 p.m.and 4:30-5:30 p.m.</P>
<P>Wednesday, January 11, 2012<BR>LVCC: 2:30-3:30 p.m.4-5 p.m and 5:30-6:30 p.m.<BR>Venetian: Open, please inquire</P>
<P>During show hours, exhibitors are more than welcome to host a press event in their booth or suite, too. To schedule a press event, please fill out the Press Conference Reservation Request From and submit to Allison Fried.</P>
<P><STRONG>Pre-Registered Media List<BR></STRONG>The highly anticipated CES pre-registered media list will be made available on November 1, 2011 to exhibitors hosting CES press events on-site. The list will also be posted to CESweb.org on December 1 for all other exhibitors– mark your calendar! All you need to access the list is your CES Exhibitor ID. Don't wait until you're at the show to get in front of the media, share your exciting news before it starts. Make sure that you use our list to outreach to target media covering your product categories.</P>
<P><STRONG>Press Kit preparation<BR></STRONG>Both the LVCC and Venetian press rooms will house paperless exhibitor press kits for the 2012 International CES. This means that exhibitors are welcome to host their press kits on USB, CD ROM or host on their own URL and accompany with a one-page spec sheet (8.5" x 11” max) that lists media contacts and the URL where your electronic press kit is located. Printed press materials greater than one page in length should be stored in the exhibitor's booth. </P>
<P>Make sure your press kit is marked clearly with the company's name and CES booth number. Press kits are a one-stop source for the media to get information about your company and products. Information included in kits should be kept simple and to the point—journalists are after hard news. </P>
<P>Most press kits typically include the following: <BR>• Recent and relevant news releases (preferably from news at the show) <BR>• Company/executive background information<BR>• Detailed product fact sheets/specs <BR>• Product images <BR>• Copies of company publications (annual reports, external magazines, etc.) <BR>• Any special events you have scheduled during the show <BR>• Media contact information </P>
<P><STRONG>Exhibitor PR Kit Distribution<BR></STRONG>Your electronic exhibitor press kits provide information about your company to the press that attend CES. All exhibitor press kits will be distributed from the press room in cubicles labeled alphabetically by company name. Only kits of exhibitors at CES are distributed from the press room. Exhibitors sharing booth space must be officially listed in the CES Directory to have their press kits distributed. </P>
<P><STRONG>Delivery Address and Timeline<BR></STRONG>Shipped electronic press kits should be marked to arrive between January 1, 2012 and January 8, 2012. Press kits may also be dropped off during press room hours throughout the show. Due to the volume of shipments, all shipments arrive at the same distribution center and are then delivered accordingly, which usually takes 2-3 days. </P>
<P><STRONG>Press Kit Mailing Address</STRONG></P>
<P>2012 International CES<BR>c/o GES Exposition Services<BR>Exhibitor Name<BR>Deliver To: PRESS ROOM, S229<BR>Las Vegas Convention Center<BR>3150 Paradise Rd. <BR>Las Vegas, NV 89109<BR>Phone: 703-907-7603<BR><A href="mailto:prcontacts@CE.org">prcontacts@CE.org</A> </P>
<P>2012 International CES <BR>c/o GES Exposition Services<BR>Exhibitor Name <BR>Deliver To: PRESS ROOM, Zeno 4601<BR>The Venetian Resort <BR>3355 Las Vegas Blvd. South<BR>Las Vegas, NV 89109<BR>Phone: 703-907-7603<BR><A href="mailto:prcontacts@CE.org">prcontacts@CE.org</A></P>
<P><STRONG>Online Press Center<BR></STRONG>News Release Distribution/Online Press Kits/Free 100-Word Exhibitor Profile<BR>Business Wire is pleased to be working with the 2012 International CES and providing exhibitors with options for distributing CES related news releases and multimedia, setting up Online Press Kits and analyzing the media that cover the show.</P>
<P>Business Wire's 2012 International CES Online Press Center makes exhibitor news available to not only attendees but also relevant trade media, industry analysts, bloggers, online media, consumers and much more worldwide.&nbsp; In addition, all news releases distributed via Business Wire automatically receive our NewsTrak measurement report.</P>
<P>The Online Press Kit by Business Wire enables exhibitors to create an effective and customizable electronic press kit accessible directly from the 2012 International CES Online Press Center.&nbsp; Each Online Press Kit also includes its own advisory via Business Wire promoting the Online Press Kit, social media sharing links and more.</P>
<P>EventTrak by Business Wire - Formulate a more effective trade show PR strategy with a detailed intelligence report.&nbsp; EventTrak provides exhibitors with pre- and post-show media and blogger coverage with direct access to contact information and articles published.&nbsp; Free with an Online Press Kit purchase or $150 alone. Free! - Business Wire is also offering all sponsors, presenters and exhibitors distribution of a free 100-word profile.</P>
<P>Email <A href="tradeshow@businesswire.com">tradeshow@businesswire.com</A> for more information on news releases, Online Press Kits, EventTrak and to receive the free 100-word profile template. </P>
<P><STRONG>Hot Product Submissions, CEA's Digital Answer Man and Press Pitch</STRONG></P>
<P><STRONG>Hot Product Submissions<BR></STRONG>Every year leading up to the International CES, and of course onsite, CEA spokespeople talk to thousands of reporters about the hot products and new trends emerging at the show. Introducing your company and new products to us before the show is an excellent way to stand out from the other 20,000 products being launched at the show, and to get your product noticed by the media.<BR>Once the show opens, we tour the show floor with our camera crew to highlight top new technologies that our member exhibitors have brought to the show. If you would like to be included in these promotions, especially if you are a smaller company, e-mail pictures and details about your hot new product to hotproducts@CE.org, and copy Allison Fried (afried@CE.org). Don't forget to include your CES Booth #.&nbsp; (All embargos will be honored.)</P>
<P><STRONG>Digital Answer Man Tour<BR></STRONG>Every year, CEA's Digital Answer Man, Jim Barry, visits national and local media outlets including TV stations, radio news broadcasts, network morning shows, specialized programs and daily newspapers to educate consumers on new products and trends in the technology industry. Barry highlights members' products and discusses top tech news in order to raise consumer interest and awareness, position CEA as a leading source of industry information, and drive traffic to retailers.&nbsp; </P>
<P>The CEA National Media Tour, aka the "Digital Answer Man Tour," travels to the international CES and to more than 50 media markets each year, where Barry showcases the latest and greatest products from CEA members. He has appeared on CNN, CNN Headline News, CNBC, Good Morning America, Fox News and countless local news programs across the nation. The CEA media tour is ongoing throughout the year. CEA members can add their products to the tour at no charge. To have your new product showcased in the media tour, contact Jim Barry or Steve Kidera.</P>
<P><STRONG>30 Second Press Video Pitch<BR></STRONG>Help the media know why they should visit your booth! Submit a 30 second video about new products you'll be unveiling at the 2012 CES, and we will feature your video in the press section of CESweb.org. Keep it brief and newsworthy, with info on booth location and new product news. Videos should be sent to PRcontacts@ce.org by December 22, 2012</P>
<P><STRONG>CES Preview Involvement<BR></STRONG>CEA has just completed construction on a state-of-the-art broadcast studio. In addition to recording media interviews, the studio will showcase new and innovative member products. In the days leading up to CES, CEA will produce several CES Preview videos for web distribution. These videos, produced with the average consumer in mind, will discuss news and information about the upcoming CES as well as showcase specific products and devices. If you would like to have your product seen and discussed, please contact Allison Fried (afried@CE.org) or Steve Kidera (<A href="mailto:skidera@CE.org">skidera@CE.org</A>).</P>
<P><STRONG>CESTV</STRONG><BR>Keep your eyes glued to CESweb.org for breaking CESTV news segments. This ten-part news series launched on November 1 and will keep you up to date with the latest 2012 CES news. A fresh CESTV segment will post every Tuesday, and run through January 3, covering topics from: The CES Conference Program, Press Specific news, South Hall, North Hall, Central Hall, The Venetian and Hilton, Overall Tech Trends, What's New, Social Media and tips for first timers. </P>
<P><STRONG>CNET Best of CES<BR></STRONG>CNET, the official live streaming and media partner for CES, will continue to produce the Best of CES Awards program for 2012. The CNET Best of CES awards name the most buzz-worthy, category-defining, innovative, and promising products at the show. The competition is judged by CNET's esteemed editorial team, published online to their widespread audience, and includes the coveted Best of Show and People's Voice awards. No submission is necessary - but make sure CNET editors know what you'll be debuting at CES. Pitch your products now!</P>
<P><STRONG>Entertainment Matters Daily, produced by Variety<BR></STRONG>January 10 - 13, 2012<BR>Variety, the leading entertainment trade magazine, will be producing printed dailies for the International CES dedicated to Entertainment Matters programming, news, events, announcements and special features. The most influential leaders in the industry have turned to Variety for timely, credible and straightforward news and analysis vital to their professions. Now they will have first hand access to the most important news and announcements impacting the entertainment industry at CES! </P>
<P>Distribution will be extensive throughout the show via publication bins and models at key distribution points. Advertising is available - front cover and premium spots as well as standard ad units in book 10,000 copies will be distributed each day of the show. In addition the printed dailies on-site at CES, over 27,000 Variety subscribers will have access to view the digital editions on-line. For more information, please contact Linda Buckley-Bruno @ 323-617-9429&nbsp; </P>
<P><STRONG>The Official International CES Daily, produced by TWICE<BR></STRONG>NEW PRODUCT DEADLINE FOR The 2012 Official International CES Daily, produced by TWICE, is MONDAY, NOVEMBER 14. <BR>If your company is an official 2012 International CES exhibitor send press releases to twicecesdaily@nbmedia.com. <BR>Or send to Steve Smith, Official CES Daily, c/o TWICE, 28 East 28th St., 12th Fl., New York, NY 10016. <BR><BR>REQUIREMENTS ARE AS FOLLOWS:<BR>• Products must be making their debut at the 2012 International CES. (Existing products that have already appeared in the market will not be considered.)<BR>• Press releases or new product info should be sent in Microsoft Word format and include the company's Booth Number<BR>• Please send high-resolution (300 dpi) images – maximum three per company please – to twicecesdaily@nbmedia.com.<BR>The deadline for New Product information and images is MONDAY, NOVEMBER 14.</P>
<P>If you have any questions please contact Steve Smith, editor in chief of TWICE, at ssmith@nbmedia.com or call 917-281-4754.</P>
